President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Louisiana due to flooding that occurred between April 25 and July 7, 2011. This declaration allows federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Gerard M. Stolar has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.